tput" data-mime-type=3D"text/markdown">
<p>Although Datasets provides a lot of low-level functionality to slice and=
 dice our data, it is often convenient to convert a <code>Dataset</code> ob=
ject to a Pandas <code>DataFrame</code> so we can access high-level APIs fo=
r data visualization. To enable the conversion, Datasets provides a <code>s=
et_format()</code> method that allows us to change the <em>output format</e=
m> of the <code>Dataset</code>. Note that this does not change the underlyi=
ng <em>data format</em> (which is an Arrow table), and you can switch to an=
other format later if needed:</p>
