<p>From the plot we see that for each emotion, most tweets are around 15 wo=
rds long and the longest tweets are well below DistilBERT's maximum context=
 size. Texts that are longer than a model's context size need to be truncat=
ed, which can lead to a loss in performance if the truncated text contains =
crucial information; in this case, it looks like that won't be an issue.</p=
>
