</div>
<div class=3D"jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class=3D"jp-InputPrompt =
jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class=3D"jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOu=
tput" data-mime-type=3D"text/markdown">
<p>Transformer models like DistilBERT cannot receive raw strings as input; =
instead, they assume the text has been <em>tokenized</em> and <em>encoded</=
em> as numerical vectors. Tokenization is the step of breaking down a strin=
g into the atomic units used in the model. There are several tokenization s=
trategies one can adopt, and the optimal splitting of words into subunits i=
s usually learned from the corpus. Before looking at the tokenizer used for=
 DistilBERT, let's consider two extreme cases: <em>character</em> and <em>w=
ord</em> tokenization.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
