<p>Here we've used PyTorch to check whether a GPU is available or not, and =
then chained the PyTorch <code>nn.Module.to()</code> method to the model lo=
ader. This ensures that the model will run on the GPU if we have one. If no=
t, the model will run on the CPU, which can be considerably slower.</p>
</div>
