<div class=3D"jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class=3D"jp-InputPrompt =
jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class=3D"jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOu=
tput" data-mime-type=3D"text/markdown">
<p>To warm up, let's retrieve the last hidden states for a single string. T=
he first thing we need to do is encode the string and convert the tokens to=
 PyTorch tensors. This can be done by providing the <code>return_tensors=3D=
"pt"</code> argument to the tokenizer as follows:</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class=3D"jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell">
<div class=3D"jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell">
