<p>Looking at the accuracy, it might appear that our model is just a bit be=
tter than random=E2=80=94but since we are dealing with an unbalanced multic=
lass dataset, it's actually significantly better. We can examine whether ou=
r model is any good by comparing it against a simple baseline. In Scikit-Le=
arn there is a <code>DummyClassifier</code> that can be used to build a cla=
ssifier with simple heuristics such as always choosing the majority class o=
r always drawing a random class. In this case the best-performing heuristic=
 is to always choose the most frequent class, which yields an accuracy of a=
bout 35%:</p>
